<title type="html"><![CDATA[06/05(Sat.)Rains in Taiwan to provide drought relief/Japan Extends State of Emergency Until Olympics(Host: Ellen)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/viewtopic.php?t=504&amp;p=526#p526"><![CDATA[
06/05(Sat.)Rain pelts down in Taiwan to provide drought relief/Japan Extends State of Emergency Until One Month Before Tokyo Olympics - The New York Times(Host: Ellen)<br /><br /><span style="color: #FF0000">There is no on-site meeting during the pandemic of COVID-19.<br /><br /><br />加入 Zoom 會議<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw">https://zoomtw.zoom.us/j/92987266213?pw</a><!-- m --> ... NKSU5MQT09<br /><br />會議 ID：929 8726 6213<br />密碼：112233<br /><br /><br />Agenda:<br />7:00-7:10 pm Opening Remarks<br />7:10-7:40 pm Session 1 Group Discussion<br />7:40-8:00 pm Presentation 1<br />8:00-8:10 pm Break<br />8:10-8:40: Session 2 Group Discussion<br />8:40-9:00 pm Presentation 2<br /><br />At the presentation the time limit is 1-2 minutes for each speaker.</span><br /><br /><br />Article 1:<br />Rain pelts down in Taiwan to provide drought relief | Taiwan News | 2021-05-30 11:07:00<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4212905">https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4212905</a><!-- m --><br /><br />For reference: <br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4212533">https://www.taiwannews.com.tw/en/news/4212533</a><!-- m --><br /><br />1. Drought happened in many countries (such like Taiwan, America, Brazil, China…) recent years, from your opinions, do you think what causes this happened?<br />2. Drought doesn’t only influence our daily life, but also has negative implications for grain cultivation, livestock and electricity generation. What is the most inconvenient thing when you face the water bans?<br />3. If your area/city is under water usage restrictions (such like two-day-a-week water bans), what will you prepare for this situation in advance and how to face it? Do you have any tip to save the water usage or energy power?<br />4. Some statements indicate that Taiwan’s water expense is too cheap and leads to residents don’t cherish/utilize water? What is your opinion about it? Do you think what government can do for it? <br />5. Drought, flood/ extremely heavy rain a...<br /><br />Article 2:<br />Japan Extends State of Emergency Until One Month Before Tokyo Olympics - The New York Times (nytimes.com)<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2021/05/28/world/asia/tokyo-olympics-covid-japan.html?searchResultPosition=4">https://www.nytimes.com/2021/05/28/worl ... Position=4</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><br />1.Do you think Japan’s emergency measures can slow down the spreading of Covid-19? <br />2.Do you think increasing inoculations can slow down/prevent Covid-19 spread out? If you are the government, what will you do to encourage people to take Covid-19 vaccine?<br />3.Do you think Japan government insists Tokyo Olympics games go on as schedule is a wise decision? Any suggestion for Japan government or Tokyo Olympics games organization?<br />4.If you are an athlete, will you still join the games? Why or why not?<br />5.If Tokyo Olympics games go on as the schedule, do you think if there will be any disaster happened?  <br /><br /><br />P.S.<br />1.參加三次後，只要繳交1,000元(學生500元)，即可成為ROYAL終身會員!<br />2.請帶著開放與熱情來參加自由的全英文會話聚會~<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.royalclub.tw/bbs3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=12531">Danny Lin</a> — Mon May 31, 2021 4:00 pm</p><hr />
